short-description: Supersprint exhaust is widely recognized as the leader in complete exhaust system upgrades - extremely high quality, well designed for optimal flow, and amazing sound. A Supersprint exhaust rewards you with a terrific sound, long lasting construction and excellent fitment. The Supersprint sound is very 'European' which fits the sporting sophistication of BMWs perfectly. Most systems are also modular - sections can be added or removed to custom tailor the exhaust sound to your preferance. Aside from 'Race' systems, their mufflers meet European noise laws so you get a refined and tuned sound without being excessively loud. Most Supersprint systems are built with larger diameter piping to improve exhaust flow which helps the engine do less work and make more horsepower! Supersprint exhausts generally run at a premium over other systems but no other system on the market can match their quality, performance, or reputation!

cleanDesc: Powerflex Rear Muffler Hanger - Street Version - E36 E46 E9X M3, E39...
short-description: BMW's original muffler hanger (part number 18201401797) works great at first but tends to fail over time, leading to sloppy exhaust movement and excessive noise. This failure is due to both heat and the heavy exhaust wearing down the hanger until it eventually tears, allowing the exhaust to shift around freely, banging off of nearby components. In order to address this common problem, Powerflex developed their own polyurethane rear muffler hanger that features a heavy-duty, yet lightweight, machined aluminum bracket. Polyurethane is significantly more resistant to the effects of heat and weight over time compared to rubber, meaning you can expect this exhaust hanger to last many times longer than your stock BMW hanger.

cleanDesc: Powerflex Rear Muffler Hanger - Race Version - E36 E46 E9X M3, E39 M...
short-description: BMW's original muffler hanger (part number 18201401797) works great at first but tends to fail over time, leading to sloppy exhaust movement and excessive noise. This failure is due to both heat and the heavy exhaust wearing down the hanger until it eventually tears, allowing the exhaust to shift around freely, banging off of nearby components. In order to address this common problem, Powerflex developed their own polyurethane rear muffler hanger that features a heavy-duty, yet lightweight, machined aluminum bracket. Polyurethane is significantly more resistant to the effects of heat and weight over time compared to rubber, meaning you can expect this exhaust hanger to last many times longer than your stock BMW hanger.

cleanDesc: Exhaust Gaskets and Hanger Package for E46 M3
short-description: A Do-It-Yourself exhaust install can be hard enough. But to stop in the middle of it to run to the dealer for gaskets, hangers, or special hardware is a major inconvenience. Don't be left taking the bus to the dealership on the hunt for parts. Get all of the parts you may need before the job begins! And with mileage we can almost gurantee that any section you remove will need to have new gaskets. Some of the gaskets are crushed to ensure a tight seal; other gaskets become stuck to their flanges. This set of hangers and gaskets for the 2001-2006 E46 M3 covers all of the sections of the exhaust, from the headers to the muffler.   The exhaust on the E46 M3 is broken up into sections -  headers - gaskets at the cylinder head and at the outlet to section 1, plus an air pump gasket  section 1 - crush gasket rings on the inlet and flange gaskets at the outlet to section 2  section 2 - flange gaskets at the inlet and steel exhaust rings at the outlet to the muffler  muffler - steel exhaust rings on the inlet with special square-shouldered nuts (included with hanger/gasket kit)   This package also includes 3 new muffler hangers and the 2 hangers in the center of the exhaust (mounted on section 1).   We also offer most of the exhaust hardware you may need -  Torx bolts and nuts for the header-section 1 connection  copper nuts for the section 1-section 2 connection (M8x30 bolts can be re-used)     2001-2006 E46 M3 coupe, convertible

E30 325i Complete Muffler Hanger Kit
short-description: This is a complete exhaust hanger and bracket kit for the 1987-1992 E30 325i models. It's all of the hangers and gaskets needed for the rear muffler and a life-saving addition to any exhaust project on your car. Any of the hardware and hangers that have been on the car for a few years are prone to rust and seizing in place. So to get them off usually means breaking or cutting one or more pieces. So having this complete E30 hanger kit on hand will allow you to finish the job without scrambling for parts later on. And new hangers are always a good idea anyway.   This 325i hanger kit includes -  front upper muffler body clamp - 18201707925 (18211707923) - x 1  front lower muffler body clamps - 18201178132 (18211178126) - x 2  rear lower muffler body clamp - 18211176029 (18211176713) - x 1  rear muffler rubber hangers - 18211712838 - x 2  center muffler rubber hanger - 18211105635 - x 1  muffler to center section seal ring (45mm) - 18111723541 x 1  muffler to center section seal ring (42mm) - 18111245960 x 1  nuts & bolts for all of the above   There is an early and late version to the muffler band clamps but the only difference we saw was more holes in the band on the early style. The early style is included in this kit which might be better because water won't get trapped between the clamp and the muffler body.   If you're removing the center section from the exhaust manifolds you can add those gaskets as well.     1987-1992    325i 325ic 325is 325ix

short-description: This set of upper and lower clamps is the perfect addition to our Hanger Kit, especially if you're going back to a stock muffler from aftermarket and no longer have these required clamps. The stock mufflers (standard E36 or M3) use this clamp method around a lip on the muffler body. But most aftermarket muffler systems don't use the clamp and bolt straight to the rubber hanger. So these stock pieces are often thrown away which will make it impossible to re-install the stock muffler. These are the OEM muffler clamps.
